    stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&gt;
    &lt;line x1=&#34;4&#34; y1=&#34;9&#34; x2=&#34;20&#34; y2=&#34;9&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;4&#34; y1=&#34;15&#34; x2=&#34;20&#34; y2=&#34;15&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;10&#34; y1=&#34;3&#34; x2=&#34;8&#34; y2=&#34;21&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;16&#34; y1=&#34;3&#34; x2=&#34;14&#34; y2=&#34;21&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;

&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;📺 &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bad_Sisters&#34;&gt;Bad Sisters&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;. The most fun I’ve had watching TV in a long time. I already miss the. Garvey sisters a tremendous amount. / 📚 &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Crummey&#34;&gt;Michael Crummey&lt;/a&gt;. Gotta be the best working novelist in Canada these days. I’m in the middle of &lt;em&gt;The Adversary&lt;/em&gt; right now, but there’s no bad book in the bunch. / 🎧 &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cliff_Martinez&#34;&gt;Cliff Martinez&lt;/a&gt; soundtracks. I use him mainly as the soundtrack for my D&amp;amp;D sessions, but have also started just listening around the house, despite the weird looks from my family.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;!-- end-chunk --&gt;
