&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://tylerhellard.com/uploads/2024/pod-loser-ep-7-facts-and-matters.mp3&#34;&gt;Facts &amp;amp; Matters&lt;/a&gt;, a mixtape. (&lt;a href=&#34;https://tylerhellard.com/podcast.xml&#34;&gt;Podcast feed&lt;/a&gt;.)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;mark&gt;NOTE:&lt;/mark&gt; Old tapes are archived &lt;a href=&#34;https://archive.org/details/pod-loser-love&#34;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;!-- end-chunk --&gt;
&lt;!-- begin-chunk data-anchor=&#34;heading-4&#34; --&gt;

&lt;h3 class=&#34;header-anchor-wrapper&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-skull-crossbones&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-skull-crossbones&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-skull-crossbones&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
  &lt;a href=&#34;#heading-4&#34; class=&#34;header-anchor-link&#34;&gt;
&lt;svg
    xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;
    width=&#34;1rem&#34; height=&#34;1rem&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34;
    stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34;
    stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&gt;
    &lt;line x1=&#34;4&#34; y1=&#34;9&#34; x2=&#34;20&#34; y2=&#34;9&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;4&#34; y1=&#34;15&#34; x2=&#34;20&#34; y2=&#34;15&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;10&#34; y1=&#34;3&#34; x2=&#34;8&#34; y2=&#34;21&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;16&#34; y1=&#34;3&#34; x2=&#34;14&#34; y2=&#34;21&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;

&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At some point we all agreed that open access to all human knowledge was a good thing and accordingly made libraries a staple of every city, every town and every school. It was one of the rare areas we managed to mostly avoid fucking up for a really, really long time. &lt;a href=&#34;https://openlibrary.org&#34;&gt;Open Library&lt;/a&gt; is, in every sense and by every definition, a library. The only real difference is that it operates at the scale of the web, which is more or less the vision of the Library of Alexandria fully realized. Woo hoo, we did it! Nice work, everybody!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Enter &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.wired.com/story/internet-archive-loses-hachette-books-case-appeal/&#34;&gt;capitalism&lt;/a&gt;; the big book publishers want it all stopped because Open Library presents &amp;ldquo;a fundamental devaluation of authors’ and publishers’ intellectual and creative investments,&amp;rdquo; which U.S. courts are so far agreeing with despite it being a very stupid point. Even worse, the ruling implies that &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.techdirt.com/2024/09/05/second-circuit-says-libraries-disincentivize-authors-to-write-books-by-lending-them-for-free/&#34;&gt;all libraries&lt;/a&gt; are, in fact, bad.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I love my &lt;a href=&#34;https://invisiblepublishing.com&#34;&gt;publisher&lt;/a&gt; (small publishers are great and do a lot operating in a system that constantly punishes them), but books are absolutely broken, both as a functional business model and as a means of creating and distributing art and ideas. Libraries are the last institution putting &lt;em&gt;value&lt;/em&gt; on them at all.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We really had our shit together there for a bit, didn&amp;rsquo;t we?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;!-- end-chunk --&gt;
&lt;!-- begin-chunk data-anchor=&#34;heading-5&#34; --&gt;

