&lt;!-- begin-chunk data-anchor=&#34;about-me&#34; --&gt;

&lt;h4 class=&#34;header-anchor-wrapper&#34;&gt;About me.
  &lt;a href=&#34;#about-me&#34; class=&#34;header-anchor-link&#34;&gt;
&lt;svg
    xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;
    width=&#34;1rem&#34; height=&#34;1rem&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34;
    stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34;
    stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&gt;
    &lt;line x1=&#34;4&#34; y1=&#34;9&#34; x2=&#34;20&#34; y2=&#34;9&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;4&#34; y1=&#34;15&#34; x2=&#34;20&#34; y2=&#34;15&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;10&#34; y1=&#34;3&#34; x2=&#34;8&#34; y2=&#34;21&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;16&#34; y1=&#34;3&#34; x2=&#34;14&#34; y2=&#34;21&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;

&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hi. I’m Tyler. I’m usually a professional &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.linkedin.com/in/tylerhellard/&#34;&gt;copywriter&lt;/a&gt;, but sometimes I write &lt;a href=&#34;/writing/&#34;&gt;other things&lt;/a&gt;, too. Once I wrote a &lt;a href=&#34;/terrypunchout/&#34;&gt;novel&lt;/a&gt; that (incredibly!) became a Canadian best seller (impossibly!) eight years after it came out.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;!-- end-chunk --&gt;
&lt;!-- begin-chunk data-anchor=&#34;heading&#34; --&gt;

&lt;h3 class=&#34;header-anchor-wrapper&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-skull-crossbones&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-skull-crossbones&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-skull-crossbones&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
  &lt;a href=&#34;#heading&#34; class=&#34;header-anchor-link&#34;&gt;
&lt;svg
    xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;
    width=&#34;1rem&#34; height=&#34;1rem&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34;
    stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34;
    stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&gt;
    &lt;line x1=&#34;4&#34; y1=&#34;9&#34; x2=&#34;20&#34; y2=&#34;9&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;4&#34; y1=&#34;15&#34; x2=&#34;20&#34; y2=&#34;15&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;10&#34; y1=&#34;3&#34; x2=&#34;8&#34; y2=&#34;21&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;16&#34; y1=&#34;3&#34; x2=&#34;14&#34; y2=&#34;21&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;

&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;!-- end-chunk --&gt;
&lt;!-- begin-chunk data-anchor=&#34;about-pop-loser&#34; --&gt;

&lt;h4 class=&#34;header-anchor-wrapper&#34;&gt;About Pop Loser.
  &lt;a href=&#34;#about-pop-loser&#34; class=&#34;header-anchor-link&#34;&gt;
&lt;svg
    xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;
    width=&#34;1rem&#34; height=&#34;1rem&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34;
    stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34;
    stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&gt;
    &lt;line x1=&#34;4&#34; y1=&#34;9&#34; x2=&#34;20&#34; y2=&#34;9&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;4&#34; y1=&#34;15&#34; x2=&#34;20&#34; y2=&#34;15&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;10&#34; y1=&#34;3&#34; x2=&#34;8&#34; y2=&#34;21&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;&lt;line x1=&#34;16&#34; y1=&#34;3&#34; x2=&#34;14&#34; y2=&#34;21&#34;&gt;&lt;/line&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;

&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Pop Loser is a blog (and, for awhile, newsletter) I&amp;rsquo;ve written on and off since 2007. It&amp;rsquo;s changed a lot over the years and I&amp;rsquo;ve burned it all to the ground five or six times. The most recent &lt;a href=&#34;/poploser/&#34;&gt;iteration&lt;/a&gt; is a bit esoteric, with a little writing and a lot of links, and includes &amp;ldquo;&lt;a href=&#34;/mixtapes/&#34;&gt;mixtapes&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;rdquo; When each volume finishes, posts are collected on an omnibus page: Vol. &lt;a href=&#34;/vol1/&#34;&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;/vol2/&#34;&gt;2&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;/vol3/&#34;&gt;3&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;/vol4/&#34;&gt;4&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;/vol5/&#34;&gt;5&lt;/a&gt;. Most previous versions of Pop Loser are archived in the following places: Newsletters #1–78 (unavailable), &lt;a href=&#34;https://web.archive.org/web/20220312222936/https://us2.campaign-archive.com/home/?u=73477be0867f67a19f1fec465&amp;amp;id=f5d72195cb&#34;&gt;#79–97&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://web.archive.org/web/20200809173730/https://www.getrevue.co/profile/poploser/#archive&#34;&gt;#98–113&lt;/a&gt; (2014–2018). &lt;a href=&#34;https://web.archive.org/web/20240000000000*/http://poploser.org/&#34;&gt;Original blog&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;a href=&#34;https://web.archive.org/web/20070528205939/http://www.spincity.org/blog/&#34;&gt;2007&lt;/a&gt;–&lt;a href=&#34;https://web.archive.org/web/20140106063005/http://poploser.org/&#34;&gt;2014&lt;/a&gt;) and &lt;a href=&#34;https://poploser.tumblr.com/&#34;&gt;Tumblr&lt;/a&gt; clone (&lt;a href=&#34;https://poploser.tumblr.com/archive&#34;&gt;2010–2014&lt;/a&gt;). From 2019 to 2024, I probably had better things to do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;!-- end-chunk --&gt;
&lt;!-- begin-chunk data-anchor=&#34;heading-1&#34; --&gt;

&lt;h3 class=&#34;header-anchor-wrapper&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-skull-crossbones&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-skull-crossbones&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-skull-crossbones&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
  &lt;a href=&#34;#heading-1&#34; class=&#34;header-anchor-link&#34;&gt;
&lt;svg
    xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;
    width=&#34;1rem&#34; height=&#34;1rem&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34;
